race.comment: COOL JUNIOR (8) is better than last start when fifth (23.33) in a NG at Maitland over 400m. Form at this distance is sound. Some good form is emerging from his last run. Has ability and is a key runner. TARAWI PRINGLE (2) was unfancied latest when jumping from this same draw but belied the odds to place (17.53) over 324m at this track in a NG. This tougher but looks a leading chance again. FUMBLES (1) was out of placings last time (17.61) at this track in a NG, finishing fourth and beaten 3 lengths. Has already won two times from this draw. With even luck and a clean start can sneak into the finish. LOGIE MAGIC (4) is last start winner who looks one of the chances.
